-- Fed taps Fischer to lead new financial stability committee
-- By Michael Flaherty
-- Fri Sep 12, 2014 02:17PM EDT
-- None



WASHINGTON, Sept 12 (Reuters) - The Federal Reserve has created a new committee on financial stability, naming Vice Chairman Stanley Fischer to lead the group.

The move shows how the Fed is looking more closely at how it can cool important parts of the financial sector before they overheat.